stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Matoimaru
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] 3 years
[Place of Birth] Higashi
[Date of Birth] Jan. 3
[Race] Oni
[Height] 172cm
[Infection Status]
Non-infected as confirmed by medical report.

[Physical Strength] Excellent 
[Mobility] Standard 
[Physical Resilience] Excellent 
[Tactical Acumen] Normal 
[Combat Skill] Standard 
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Excellent

This nomadic warrior from the Far East joined Rhodes Island by sheer chance.
What she lacks in strategic acumen, she makes up with a mean giant sickle swing.

Imaging tests on this Operator show clear outlines of internal organs, with no abnormal dark spots or shadows. No unusual traces of Originium particles present in the circulatory system, no signs of infection, confirming this operator as uninfected. 

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 0% 
Operator Matoimaru showed no symptoms of Oripathy. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.12u/L 
Operator Matoimaru rarely comes into contact with Originium.

Matoimaru is a magnificent warrior from the Far East.
She is simpleminded and prone to deception. She does catch on, but a new trick will fool her again.
Her hobbies, at which she excels, are sparring, soccer, and floral arrangement. She has been known to organize events around these subjects, though her idea of organization is typically dragging people kicking and screaming into it.

The Oni are still a mystery to most people. Aside from living in the Far East, there seems to be little in common among the race. 
However, Matoimaru is yet even more different from other Oni: Her bloodlust makes her performance on the battlefield strikingly unique, though it seems she's not aware of this fact.

Many Operators think Matoimaru is crude and unrefined, but they are mistaken.
They just need to check out her floral arrangements, on display every Saturday at 3pm. 
The beauty she can create is positively astonishing.

Matoimaru is obviously self-conscious about her flaws: She is not good at controlling her strength or at critical thinking. 
She took up floral arrangement to refine herself and to show the others they don't need to fear her. 
Despite this, she's remains quite gullible. At least she has learned to question the idea that she must be a great thinker in order to survive. 
As far as she is concerned, her ideal companion would be someone who won't deceive or betray her, and will stay with her and guide her. How wonderful that would be...

skins.description:
An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

modules.desc:
Operator Matoimaru has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude in wielding her naginata to penetrate enemy formations.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Guard Operator during field operations to exercise Dreadnought responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

The young Oni warrior passes by this street every day, sticking to the glass of the florist's shop to see the new ikebana arrangement, before leaving satisfied. It is difficult to identify the age of an Oni, but she carries a bamboo naginata on her back, indicating that she is still a musha in training. Our florist has a secret rule: Oni are not allowed inside because their actions are uncouth, and if they are not careful, they will destroy months of the flower arrangers' efforts in the blink of an eye. We are justifiably cautious, as we never know if they might have the support of their kin from the underworld behind them.
There is an alley on the other side of the florist, and misbehaving students use it as a hideout. They demand money from their frail and weak classmates, throwing them to the ground or stomping on them. This Wednesday evening, I saw a little boy with a backpack run by the window with a sullen, tear-stained face and a bruised nose. On Thursday, he passed by this place with the Oni, but soon turned back alone and squirmed back into the alley. 
 On Friday afternoon, I was helping the master arrange flowers when I saw people squatting along the side of the street with water pipes, wine bottles, crowbars, and the like. Before we could call the police, the person they were waiting for arrived. The Oni musha accompanied the little boy from school just like yesterday. When they got to our window, the little boy suddenly began to pick up his pace, and the teens who were bullying him quickly surrounded him. 
They were almost ready to kill the Oni. The Oni's bamboo naginata managed to block a few blows, but was broken into several pieces by their sheer brute force. 
Then, that was the first time I saw an ‘Oni.’ 
The Oni musha who had lost her weapon raised her fists, tearing through metal with her bare knuckles, smearing her own blood in the eyes of her opponents, lashing out with her knees and feet when her fists were blocked, striking out with her horns when her legs were restrained, biting with her teeth when her horns were blocked. When the whistle signaling the police's arrival came at last, only one was still standing – the Oni. 
She wiped the corners of her bleeding lips emotionlessly, like the legendary man-eating fiends of lore. The people were intimidated by her silence and kept their distance to avoid her, pointing at her from behind windows and doors. 
Then, my master opened the door of the flower shop and walked out, sliding a bamboo leaf freshly-folded into an appropriate shape into the palm of her hand. 
The young Oni warrior blinked, as if she had woken up from a nightmare, carefully closed her fist, and smiled at my master.

voice_lines.voiceText: Doctor, you gotta be hungry! Try some of my onigiri. They're great!
I've got a lotta hobbies: martial art sparring, soccer… Oh! And Ikebana! Some took me as a warrior with more brawn than brains, and I'd say they're the ones who's got a fat head!
My race eats other races? That's some old crap! Who told you that? Tch, those cowards, cooking up this nonsense behind my back. When I find'em, I'll give'em a lesson they'll never forget!
I'm born with this self-healing body. Even if I take a few cuts in the fight, the wounds will close back up in no time.

Hey, Doctor, Rhodes Island's got a soccer tournament! C'mon, let's sign up together! No need to think twice! Just put me in your team, and it's in the bag. You'd better work your brain elsewhere, like a cool victory pose!
You don't even recognize me on the battlefield? I just start cutting through enemies with a face as cold as my blade? Wow! Sounds hella badass! Wish I could watch myself out there.
I got this problem where I kinda end up breaking stuff, so I'm working with my Ikebana teacher to control my strength. Besides, getting surrounded by all those pretty flowers makes me real happy!
Strategy? Ehh, not really my forte. That's why I keep hopping right into the enemy's plans. But you, Doctor, you always stop me right before I lose my mind. Real nice to have you by my side.

Actually, I've always been a gullible dummy. Got duped so bad in the past that I almost got myself killed a few times. But now I, Matoimaru, swear loyalty to you, Doctor! Because I know you'll never betray me.
Grr... Hey, no falling asleep, Doctor! I need a listener or I'm gonna die of boredom!
Matoimaru, here to join Rhodes Island! My blade is at your command, Doctor!
More fancy skills to beat those bad guys with!
Doctor, put my strength to good work. That'll be the respect I deserve.
Doctor, please stand back a bit. I don't want to hurt you when swinging my naginata. But I, Matoimaru, will bring us every victory in your name.
Hah hah! You all look pretty tough. How about a warm-up with me?
Ugh, you want me to play captain? Then how am I suppose to throw myself into the battle!?
You guys ready to rumble? Then what are we waiting for!?
Sorry to keep you waiting, bad guys!
I'm over here.
Just how long until it's my turn?
Love that battlefield smell.
Make 'em shake in their boots!
Standing up to me? Haha, Ballsy!
Ready to meet your demise?
My blade shall rip you and your toy to ribbons!
You end here!
A sea of fire and a mountain of blades... Now that's what I call a fight. This is the battlefield I've always dreamed of.
Doctor, I got 'em all! Huh? what happened here? Everything's busted… Um, wait a second, did I do it...?
I'll get 'em before they escape! Can't call the battle over unless we got every last of 'em!
Retreat! I'll cover your escape. Make sure you don't get hit!
Agh! Ow! My horn...!
Huh?
What's with that smile on your face? Anything to share with me?
Arknights.
Hey, Doctor, how does Rhodes Island celebrate the New Year? Oh, anything is welcome? Haha, alright then, I'll put together a soccer match with Matterhorn and the others! Make sure you come to watch!
Uh huh, I'm listening.
Happy birthday, Doctor! I wanted to fill your office with flowers, but my teacher said restraint is the first rule of Ikebana. So I made you this! And it should fit just fine on your desk!
This blade brings nothing but trouble when I'm holding it. Good thing I can trust you to tell me where to swing it. That way, nothing can go wrong!
